  <context>
    <background>
      The C# enum `ActionType` predates R7's dispatch reform. Its values name executors (`AiAnalysis`, `AiCompletion`,
      `Condition`, `Start`, `ReturnResponse`, ...) — the "Action" prefix is misleading because the Action concept now
      refers to a separate Dataverse entity (`sprk_analysisaction`) carrying prompt templates. Renaming aligns the type
      name with its true role (dispatch axis). Per Q17 in spec.md, full rename across BFF is the chosen disposition.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="020" status="must-be-complete">Reference inventory.</dependency>
      <dependency task="021" status="must-be-complete">Rename strategy + execution plan.</dependency>
    </dependencies>
    <related-work>
